(64, 4, 2006, 4, 12, 9, '1327530203.jpg', 'Val Cooper claims she didn''t know that the tags also had the ability to ''shock'' the wearer.  Kitty Pryde vehemently doubts that.  We find that she was not lying when she is seen complaning to General Lazer about the fact that she was not told.<br /><br />\r\nHank McCoy confirms that the tags did not kill Jazz.<br /><br />\r\nVal tells the General that she is losing what little trust the mutants had in her.  General Lazer does not appear to care and seems to welcome the idea of ''controlling'' them.<br /><br />\r\nWhen Erg attempts to defy and attack Colonel Reyes when he orders them to disperse General Lazer orders that Erg be shocked.<br /><br />\r\nWhen they realise they can''t remove the tags themselves because they are bonded to the bone, Mister M uses his powers to remove them to the annoyance of General Lazer.<br /><br />\r\nMister M then leads an exodus from the Institute through the walls as the gates are blockaded by Sentinels and O*N*E personnel.<br /><br />\r\nAfter flushing the miniature Jazz down the toilet, Johnny Dee encounters Leech whom he manages to sneak some DNA off of.<br /><br />\r\nVal allows Cyclops an opportunity to try and talk the mutants back into the compound but Erg attacks Cyclops.  Emma finds she cannot control Erg as his mind appears to be ''elsewhere'', when Cyclops retaliates against Erg, Mister M shields him declaring "No one will harm my people!"', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1327530203":{"comic":"9","issue_number":"4","year_published":"2006","month_published":"4","day_published":"12","image":"1327530203.jpg","comic_summary":"Val Cooper claims she didn''t know that the tags also had the ability to ''shock'' the wearer.  Kitty Pryde vehemently doubts that.  We find that she was not lying when she is seen complaning to General Lazer about the fact that she was not told.\\r\\nHank McCoy confirms that the tags did not kill Jazz.\\r\\nVal tells the General that she is losing what littl