(68, 20, 2005, 11, 9, 13, '1327530961.jpg', 'Two Years Ago: An old man is shown entering a ransacked and abandoned church where he pleads with God for answers and help.  When none are coming he goes to commit suicide but is stopped by a large figure back lit by a blinding light which he takes to be a sign from God.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nPresent Day: The Xavier Institute is thrown into chaos as the students and teacher discover than most of them have lost their mutant abilities.  The panic of the students threatens to overwhelm Emma Frost and the other telepaths.  She struggles to Cerebro calling for the Stepford Cuckoos as she goes.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nCerebro shows a 91.4% decrease in the worlds mutant population.  Combining her powers with the Cuckoos they cause the inhabitants to sleep.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTwo Days Later:  After hearing Scott and Emma fight over her firing Danielle Moonstar because she is no longer a mutant, he calls X-23 and tells her she needs to come back.  She refuses and points out that the people after her will find her, she throws her phone away.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nTwo Weeks after M-Day:  Scott and Emma open the front door of the Institute to find Jay Gutherie on the front step bleeding from where his wings had been amputated.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1327530961":{"comic":"13","issue_number":"20","year_published":"2005","month_published":"11","day_published":"9","image":"1327530961.jpg","comic_summary":"Two Years Ago: An old man is shown entering a ransacked and abandoned church where he pleads with God for answers and help.  When none are coming he goes to commit suicide but is stopped by a large figure back lit by a blinding light which he takes to be a sign from God.\\r\\n\\r\\nPresent Day: The Xavier Institute is thrown into chaos as the students and teacher discover than most of them have lost their mutant abilities.  The panic of the students threatens to overwhelm Emma Frost and th