(52, 209, 2010, 9, 15, 6, '1370118508.jpg', '<p>Following the events of the previous issue, Jamie and X-Factor follow Hera and Pip to Nevada in order to get some answers.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> Earlier Jamie discovered that Rahne was pregnant. Unfortunately a moment of confusion causes Rictor to accuse Jamie of sleeping with her, or one of his dupes.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> Back to the present and Jamie is in search of Layla and Longshot who have both vanished. He soon finds them shooting craps... and winning. Despite not being happy about Layla an Longshot off gambling when Longshot is supposed to be getting a read off the amulet, he soon realises that Layla is right and that he is more likely to find a lead if he sticks near Longshot and his probability influence.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> A Doctor Foster recognises the photo of Hela but warns them off but informs them that Hela will approach them if she notices them.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> Jamie sends Longshot back into the casino to keep winning in the hopes that Hela will notice them.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> <br /><br /> Whilst the rest of the gang are enjoying Longshots winnings, Jamie and Shatterstar encounter some viking like warriors who wind up causing a fight with them. It is soon revealed that they are there to ensure that they join their ranks in service of their mistress.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, 'Array', 2, '{"1325112434":{"reporter_id":"737699300","id":"0","details":"gfddgfdfg","event_id":"52"},"1325372568":{"reporter_id":"100002077828287","id":"3","details":"fdbdbffbd","event_id":"52"}}', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(169, 12, 1965, 1, 10, 1, '1372023363.jpg', '<p>Whilst working in his lab, Ant Man recieves a distress call from some ants. &nbsp;He rallies the Avengers but he is ridiculed when they learn the call came from tiny insects. &nbsp;Having been insulted Ant Man sends the Avengers away so he can deal with the situation on his own.</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile Mole Man and his slaves are working on a machine that will make him the ''undisputed Master of the Surface''. &nbsp;It is an Atomic Gyroscope that will increase the speed of the Earth''s rotation until everything on the surface is destroyed but those at the core of the Earth are protected.</p>\r\n<p>Having been abandoned by the Avengers and The Wasp, Ant Man tracks down the location of the distress signal, he is soon drawn to the Mole Man and his device. &nbsp;Mole man sends his slaves to overwhelm Ant Man and he is soon overcome.</p>\r\n<p>Eventually those on the surface become aware of the increase in the Earth''s rotation, the Avengers are shamed by their casual dismissal of Ant Man''s warnings but vow to make it right. &nbsp;The Wasp uses the Image Projector invented to find the Hulk (Avengers #3) to project herself and find the location of Ant Man and the identity of their foe: Mole Man.</p>\r\n<p>They plan to utilise New Transitorized Fox-Hole Diggers made for the army by Tony Stark but they are attacked by the Mole Man''s slaves. &nbsp;After a prolonged fight they manage to defeat the slaves but they vanish in a mist.</p>\r\n<p>Captain America and Rick Jones head off to get thet Fox-Hole diggers where they encounter some thugs trying to steal them but manage to deal with them.</p>\r\n<p>The Avengers complete the Fox-Hole Diggers and head to the place they need to dig as determined by Thor and his hammer.</p>\r\n<p>Elsewhere Mole Man is furious that his slaves have returned as he hadn''t ordered that. &nbsp;He is confronted by the Red Ghost who claims he managed to phase them through the Earth with his abilities. &nbsp;He proposes that they join forces but the Avengers soon arrive.</p>\r\n<p>As the rest of the Avengers hold off the Red Ghost and the Mole Man''s men, The Wasp tracks down the imprisoned Ant Man who then climbs inside the Atomic Gyroscope and disables it. &nbsp;The Mole Man is able to escape with help from the Red Ghost and his ability to phase.</p>\r\n<p>The Avengers agree to all apologise to Ant Man for the way they treated him.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, 'Array', 0, '', 'published', '2013-06-23 14:36:03'),
