(69, 1, 1941, 3, 1, 12, '1369829556.jpg', '<p>This volume contains three stories about Captain America (including his origins) and two other stories. In the first story the Second World War occurring in Europe. The US military is finding spies in their ranks and they turn to the FBI for an answer. Enter Steve Rodgers. A young man rejected from the army due to his frailness. He is offered the chance to become America''s hero by use of a special serum. Once the serum is proved viable and Steve is now a super soldier, one of the observers reveals himself to be a spy and kills the lead doctor. Before dying the doctor names Steve; ''Captain America''.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> He goes on to perform various heroic deeds when he discovered donning his costume by a patriotic young boy named ''Bucky''. Captain America takes the young boy on as his sidekick.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> In the second story, Cap'' and Bucky investigate a pair of future telling gentlemen who have mysteriously predicted various attacks and accidents on the US. Their investigation leads them to discover a ring of Nazi spies.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> The third story is not a comic, it tells of a night where Cap'' prevents a spy from poisoning the entire army camp.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> The fourth story is along similar lines where the Captain and Bucky investigate a series of murders and uncover another spy cell.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> The fifth story reveals the Red Skull who is assassinating various military leaders. He is later revealed to be the designer of an experimental airplane the army was testing and a spy for the Fuhrer.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 100002077828287, 'Array', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(70, 1, 1963, 9, 10, 1, '1327760756.jpg', '<p>When Loki tries to trick Thor in to attacking The Hulk they band together with Iron Man, Ant Man and The Wasp to for: The Avengers!</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, 'Array', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(72, 3, 1964, 1, 10, 1, '1327763596.jpg', '<p>Still smarting from his treatment by the Avengers in the previous issue, The Hulk teams up with Namor, The Sub-Mariner.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, 'Array', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(73, 4, 1964, 3, 10, 1, '1327763697.jpg', 'In the wake of his defeat in the previous issue, Namor, whilst venting his anger comes across some locals worshipping a frozen being. He tosses the frozen cube into the ocean where it begins to melt. The Avengers rescue the trapped individual to discover it is the long lost Captain America. <br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nOn arrival back in manhattan, the Avengers are attacked and it is up to Rick Jones and Captain America to save the day. Eventually they run across Namor. Namor is run off when the alien who had attacked them gets his ship working and flees the planet.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1327763697":{"comic":"1","issue_number":"4","year_published":"1964","month_published":"3","day_published":"10","image":"1327763697.jpg","comic_summary":"In the wake of his defeat in the previous issue, Namor, whilst venting his anger comes across some locals worshipping a frozen being. He tosses the frozen cube into the ocean where it begins to melt. The Avengers rescue the trapped individual to discover it is the long lost Captain America. \\r\\n\\r\\nOn arrival back in manhattan, the Avengers are attacked and it is up to Rick Jones and Captain America to save the day. Eventually they run across Namor. Namor is run off when the alien who had attacked them gets his ship working and flees the planet.","arc_events":false,"characters":["51"],"character_events":[""],"arc_id":false,"previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(74, 5, 1964, 5, 10, 1, '1327763764.jpg', '10 May 1964  Following the battle between the Hulk and the Fantastic Four in The Fantastic Four #26, The Avengers reconvene back at Tony Stark''s mansion, from there they disperse to deal with their own challenges and daily lives.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nA few days later a mysterious noise causes damage at one of Tony Stark''s weapons factories and he goes to investigate.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWhilst investigating an ant hill, Ant-Man and The Wasp are nearly buried when the same sound causes the ant hill to collapse around them.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThor notices the sounds reported in the newspaper and decides to summon the Avengers. He seeks out Captain America who is training Rick Jones and his friends. Whilst explaining the situation they hear the noise and return to Tony Stark''s mansion to assemble. Together they manage to triangulate the origin of the sounds to a missile installation.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThe installation is under the command of General Ross and strange green hill appears to be growing on the base. At the same time Bruce Banner turns up.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBeneath the surface, the Lava Men are using crude machines to raise the green hill or ''Living Rock'' to the surface. They feel they are being menaced by the rock and are trying to save themselves by sending it to the surface.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nOne of the Lava Men, Molto, speaks in defence of the surface people based on his encounters with Thor in Journey Into Mystery #97 "Thor vs. The Lava Men". He is silenced by the Lava Men''s Witch Doctor who Molto accuses of wanting to start a war between the Lava Men and Surface People.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nJust as the General orders missiles to ring the green hill, which Banner has said might be radio-active, the Avengers arrive.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIron Man goes first to investigate, protected from the radiation in his suit of armour. He attempts to blast past the outer layers to see what is beneath, but the Lava Men see this as an attack. Iron Man tries to talk them down but they still attack. He is rescued by Thor and Captain America.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nAs the only one capable of surviving the heat of the lava, Thor continues alone and asks to speak to the ruler of the Lava men. They refuse and attack, but flee when it becomes apparent that Thor will survive. Thor approaches the Witch Doctor and the ruler of the Lava Men they show him the Living Rock they explain that they are trying to remove the rock as it is causing damage to their domain. Thor threatens to destroy the rock but the Witch Doctor stops him and gives him the history of the rock.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nHe explains that striking the rock will cause an explosion that would destroy the planet. Thor tries to get them to consider another way but the Witch Doctor refuses and calls reinforcements. The reinforcements are blocked by Captain America, he soon joined by Rick Jones and Iron Man.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nAnt-Man and the Wasp investigate the rock from the surface, Ant-Man believes he has found the spot where the rock can safely be struck and destroyed without destroying the planet. They seek out Thor so he can deliver the blow with his hammer.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nOn the surface Bruce Banner becomes the Hulk again and spies the Avengers. The Avengers in turn spy the Hulk and attempt to remove him from the scene but the Hulk retaliates.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThor attempts to stop the Hulk whilst the others fallback, but the Witch Doctor seals him in. A freak occurrence causes Thor to revert to his alter-ego, Don Blake, too weak to move.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWithout Thor to destroy the Living Rock they trick the Hulk into destroying it.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThor manages to change just in time. He delivers a warning to the Lava Men to stay away from the surface.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWhilst Thor rejoins the Avengers, Betty Ross finds an injured Bruce Banner, she believes the Hulk hurt him. She takes him away to tend to his injuries whilst the Avengers head off on another mission.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1327763764":{"comic":"1","issue_number":"5","year_published":"1964","month_published":"5","day_published":"10","image":"1327763764.jpg","comic_summary":"10 May 1964  Following the battle between the Hulk and the Fantastic Four in The Fantastic Four #26, The Avengers reconvene back at Tony Stark''s mansion, from there they disperse to deal with their own challenges and daily lives.\\r\\n\\r\\nA few days later a mysterious noise causes damage at one of Tony Stark''s weapons factories and he goes to investigate.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhilst investigating an ant hill, Ant-Man and The Wasp are nearly buried when the same sound causes the ant hill to collapse around them.\\r\\n\\r\\nThor notices the sounds reported in the newspaper and decides to summon the Avengers. He seeks out Captain America who is training Rick Jones and his friends. Whilst explaining the situation they hear the noise and return to Tony Stark''s mansion to assemble. Together they manage to triangulate the origin of the sounds to a missile installation.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe installation is under the command of General Ross and strange green hill appears to be growing on the base. At the same time Bruce Banner turns up.\\r\\n\\r\\nBeneath the surface, the Lava Men are using crude machines to raise the green hill or ''Living Rock'' to the surface. They feel they are being menaced by the rock and are trying to save themselves by sending it to the surface.\\r\\n\\r\\nOne of the Lava Men, Molto, speaks in defence of the surface people based on his encounters with Thor i