nce causes Thor to revert to his alter-ego, Don Blake, too weak to move.\\r\\n\\r\\nWithout Thor to destroy the Living Rock they trick the Hulk into destroying it.\\r\\n\\r\\nThor manages to change just in time. He delivers a warning to the Lava Men to stay away from the surface.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhilst Thor rejoins the Avengers, Betty Ross finds an injured Bruce Banner, she believes the Hulk hurt him. She takes him away to tend to his injuries whilst the Avengers head off on another mission.","arc_events":false,"characters":["51"],"character_events":[""],"arc_id":false,"previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(75, 6, 1964, 7, 10, 1, '1327763858.jpg', '10 July 1964  After testing some new features that Iron Man added to Captain America''s shield and gloves, Captain America finds himself suffering depression over his displacement in time and loss of his old partner Bucky. Rick Jones attempts to comfort him and remind him that he is supposed to be training to be his sidekick. Captain America expresses his wish to confront the person that caused Bucky''s death.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn the South American Jungle Baron Zemo rules over a primitive tribe as he awaits supplies and news from civilisation. The newspaper in the supplies reveals the re-emergence of Captain America who is responsible for his being trapped beneath the mask he wears. He also reveals that he was responsible for the Captain''s time in frozen stasis and the loss of Bucky. He enlists the pilot who delivered the supplies to return him to civilisation so he can get revenge on Captain America.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBack in New York the Teen Brigade are trying to reach the Avengers due to various villains terrorising the city. The Black Knight is flying over the city spraying the same adhesive that caused Baron Zemo''s mask to become attached to his face.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nOnce the Black Knight runs out of adhesive the Melter arrives destroying police weapons and then continuing to spray more of the adhesive that the Black Knight was spraying.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nRadioactive Man is also in the city spraying the adhesive and causing mayhem.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn order to defeat their enemies they find they must change tactics as their usual targets have developed counter attacks, such as Radioactive Man being able to repel Thor''s hammer or The Melter being able to damage Iron Man''s armour.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nDuring the fight, Ant-Man and Captain America find themselves trapped in the Adhesive X. Iron Man has to cut the surrounding concrete and use a tow truck to remove them from the scene as the Avengers retreat.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWhilst the Avengers are retreating, Radioactive Man comments that they should follow them quickly before they find a solution for Adhesive X. Baron Zemo realises that if the Avengers can create a solution then he finally be free from his mask, he begins secretly plotting to steal it.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBack at Tony Stark''s mansion, the Avengers are unable to free Ant-Man and Captain America. The Wasp has the idea to call the police to ask the advice of a criminal called Paste-Pot Pete who is the Worlds Greatest Authority on Pastes and Adhesives.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIron Man then flies off to retrieve the Super-Disolver that Paste-Pot Pete offers in lieu of a reduced sentence.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nOnce Captain America and Ant-Man are free they decide to switch their opponents around so they cannot exploit their tactics.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nCaptain America, believing he knows who is leading the Master''s of Evil, calls in the Teen Brigade to carry out their own mission. They quietly incapacitate Zemo''s pilot and switch out the Adhesive X for the Super Dissolver. This causes the Master''s of Evil to unwittingly free the citizens they had previously trapped with Adhesive X.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThe Black Knight is then taken down by Thor, Radioactive Man is taken down by the teamwork of Iron Man and Ant-Man. Iron Man is forced to confront The Melter but is able to defeat him.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nAs the Teen Brigade leave to rejoin Captain America they are caught by Baron Zemo who hypnotises them into obeying him. They are rescued by Captain America who at long last confronts Zemo and eventually drives him off as Zemo''s pilot rescues him. Captain America is rescued by Ant-Man and The Wasp.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nAnt-Man captures the pilot as Iron Man reverses the hypnotism on the Teen Brigade.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nCaptain America reveals that the Teen Brigade switched out the Super Dissolver that Baron Zemo was going to use to remove his mask with a canister of tear gas making it easy for the police to find him. Expand Edit Report Delete<br /><br /><br />\r\nIssue: #7<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\n10 August 1964  Following the events of Iron Man #56, Iron Man is brought before a Special Board of Inquiry so he can explain why he failed to answer an Avengers Alarm previously.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIron Man is suspended from the Avengers for a week which he accepts feeling he deserves it.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nMeanwhile, in Asgard, Odin has banished The Enchantress and The Executioner to Earth for attacking Thor in Journey Into Mystery #103. The exiled pair find themselves on Earth where they soon realise they are ill equipped to blend in on Earth, seeing the recent defeat of Baron Zemo in a newspaper they decide to seek him out to aid them.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBaron Zemo is approached by projected images of The Enchantress and The Executioner. They offer to join forces and help Zemo defeat Captain America.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nAs the Avengers go their separate ways to deal with personal chores, Captain America and Rick Jones are approached by a man claiming to be the former second in command to Dr. Zemo. He tells Captain America where he can find Baron Zemo as an act of repentance for his crimes as a Nazi. As Captain America heads off the Nazi reveals himself to be The Executioner in disguise baiting a trap.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWhilst Thor is flying through the air he hears a voice calling for him, he discovers The Enchantress who immediately ensnares him making him obey her. She places Thor in a trance where he is tricked into believing that the Avengers are evil, dangerous menaces and himself as the only person capable of defeating them. When he awakes he heads off to defeat them.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn the South American Jungle, Baron Zemo watches as Captain America parachutes into his trap. But the Captain manages to survive the initial trap and moves onto defeat his aboriginal soldiers who are now armed with machine guns. But the Captain falls into a trap designed for large carnivores.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBack in New York, Thor attacks the Ant Man and The Wasp by luring them into a trap. Iron Man sees the reports on the television and decides to aid them regardless of his banishment.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nNearby The Enchantress and The Executioner are watching, whilst checking on the battle between Baron Zemo and Captain America, The Enchantress is disgusted that Captain America is trapped and Zemo still hasn''t defeated him. She uses her powers to cause a cave in but Captain America uses his shield to protect himself and then use the fallen rocks to escape.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBaron Zemo attempts to use his Vibra-Gun on Captain America, but Captain America is faster defeats them and uses the gun on them. Baron Zemo attempts to flee using his secret plane but Captain America uses the magnets in his shield to latch on and travel back with him secretly.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn New York, Thor has managed to break out of Iron Man''s hold and continue attacking. Realising that Thor must be under some form of hypnosis he blinds Thor with the sun''s reflection breaking the spell of The Enchantress. <br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nSensing Baron Zemo approaching she guides him to the Avengers but Captain America makes his move forcing him to flee. They join up with Baron Zemo to flee only for Tho