(78, 1, 2004, 12, 1, 14, '1328058121.jpg', 'Max Dillon a.k.a Electro, is discussing a job with a mysterious stranger hidden by the shadows.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nAt the Ryker''s Maximum Security Installation known as The Raft, Matt Murdock and Foggy Nelson, accompanied by Luke Cage are greeted by Jessica Drew.  As she escorts them through the facility Luke sees that they have the Purple Man there.  Jessica assures them that they are held deep within the facility and kept dosed on drugs to keep them compliant.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nAs they reach the lower levels and the cells the power fails and they are plunged into darkness unaware that the rest of New York is also in darkness.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nHaving interrupted his night with MJ, Peter dons his Spiderman costume and heads out to investigate the visible electrical disturbance at The Raft by clinging to a helicopter heading that way.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nOn route the helicopter is struck by a lightning bolt and crashes into The Raft.  Spiderman is pulled from the water by the chopper''s passenger, Captain America.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nBack inside Electro has freed a specific prisoner as well as the others.  He warns them that they all owe him.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nMatt Murdock orders Foggy to stay behind Luke Cage as he is the bodyguard as he has Jessica take to the man they came to see, Robert Reynolds, The Sentry, a man who turned himself in because he claimed he killed his wife.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 100002077828287, '{"1328058121_100002077828287":{"comic":"14","issue_number":"1","year_published":"2004","month_published":"12","day_published":"1","image":"1328058121.jpg","comic_summary":"Max Dillon a.k.a Electro, is discussing a job with a mysterious stranger hidden by the shadows.\\r\\n\\r\\nAt the Ryker''s Maximum Security Installation known as The Raft, Matt Murdock and Foggy Nelson, accompanied by Luke Cage are greeted by Jessica Drew.  As she escorts them through the facility Luke sees that they have the Purple Man there.  Jessica assures them that they are held deep within the facility and kept dosed on drugs to keep them compliant.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs they reach the lower levels and the cells the power fails and they are plunged into darkness unaware that the rest of New York is also in darkness.\\r\\n\\r\\nHaving interrupted his night with MJ, Peter dons his Spiderman costume and heads out to investigate the visible electrical disturbance at The Raft by clinging to a helicopter heading that way.\\r\\n\\r\\nOn route the helicopter is struck by a lightning bolt and crashes into The Raft.  Spiderman is pulled from the water by the chopper''s passenger, Captain America.\\r\\n\\r\\n","arc_events":false,"characters":["51"],"character_events":[""],"arc_id":false,"previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false},"1328218660_100002077828287":{"comic":"14","issue_number":"1","year_published":"2004","month_published":"12","day_published":"1","image":"1328058121.jpg","summary":"Max Dillon a.k.a Electro, is discussing a job with a mysterious stranger hidden by the shadows.\\r\\n\\r\\nAt the Ryker''s Maximum Security Installation known as The Raft, Matt Murdock and Foggy Nelson, accompanied by Luke Cage are greeted by Jessica Drew.  As she escorts them through the facility Luke sees that they have the Purple Man there.  Jessica assures them that they are held deep within the facility and kept dosed on drugs to keep them compliant.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs they reach the lower levels and the cells the power fails and they are plunged into darkness unaware that the rest of New York is also in darkness.\\r\\n\\r\\nHaving interrupted his night with MJ, Peter dons his Spiderman costume and heads out to investigate the visible electrical disturbance at The Raft by clinging to a helicopter heading that way.\\r\\n\\r\\nOn route the helicopter is struck by a lightning bolt and crashes into The Raft.  Spiderman is pulled from the water by the chopper''s passenger, Captain America.\\r\\n\\r\\nBack inside Electro has freed a specific prisoner as well as the others.  He warns them that they all owe him.\\r\\n\\r\\nMatt Murdock orders Foggy to stay behind Luke Cage as he is the bodyguard as he has Jessica take to the man they came to see, Robert Reynolds, The Sentry, a man who turned himself in because he claimed he killed his wife.","arc_events":[""],"arc_id":null,"previous_event_id":null,"next_event_id":null,"character_events":{"69":"Electro takes a job which appears to involve breaking a specific prisoner out of The Raft, a Maximum Security Prison Installation which is a part of Ryker''s Island.  He offers to do the job with or without his mask, but when they leave it to him he chooses the mask.<br \\/>\\r\\n<br \\/>\\r\\nAfter freeing the prisoners and collecting his target, he tells the remaining prisoners that they owe him.","64":"Luke Cage is hired by Matt Murdock as a bodyguard for himself and Foggy Nelson as they visit The Raft.  He is not pleased to find the Purple Man alive and a prisoner suggesting they should be killed.","63":"Jessica is their assigned S.H.I.E.L.D super powered hero for the trip.  It is policy for them to be accompanied by one.<br \\/>\\r\\n<br \\/>\\r\\n"}}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(79, 5, 2005, 4, 27, 14, '1328058648.jpg', 'Whilst Iron Man, Spiderman and Captain America deal with an attacking T-Rex like dinosaur, Luke Cage and Spider Woman deal with a feral Wolverine who has stumbled upon them and tried to attack them, but Spider Woman quickly disables him with his own claws.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nOnce they have calmed him down he explains that he was there tracking Lykos who Wolverine suspects is involved in the breakout at The Raft.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThey are suddenly surrounded and attacked by Savage Land Mutates.  On discovering that many of their powers aren''t working they are made to sleep by a Mutate.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThey wake up to find them selves hanging by their arms from the ceiling, naked.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nCaptain America demands to speak to Lykos who appears and informs them that he was forced by the US government to murder other mutants.  Lykos orders them killed but Tony Stark activates his armour which builds itself up and begins to attack the mutates.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn the ensuing battle Lykos transforms into Sauron but is shot by a S.H.I.E.L.D agent that arrives on the scene with a team.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1328058648_737699300":{"comic":"14","issue_number":"5","year_published":"2005","month_published":"4","day_published":"27","image":"1328058648.jpg","comic_summary":"Whilst Iron Man, Spiderman and Captain America deal with an attacking T-Rex like dinosaur, Luke Cage and Spider Woman deal with a feral Wolverine who has stumbled upon them and tried to attack them, but Spider Woman quickly disables him with his own claws.\\r\\n\\r\\nOnce they have calmed him down he explains that he was there tracking Lykos who Wolverine suspects is involved in the breakout at The Raft.\\r\\n\\r\\nThey are suddenly surrounded and attacked by Savage Land Mutates.  On discovering that many of their powers aren''t working they are made to sleep by a Mutate.\\r\\n\\r\\nThey wake up to find them selves hanging by their arms from the ceiling, naked.\\r\\n\\r\\nCaptain America demands to speak to Lykos who appears and informs them that he was forced by the US government to murder other mutants.  Lykos orders them killed but Tony Stark activates his armour which builds itself up and begins to attack the mutates.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn the ensuing battle Lykos transforms into Sauron but is shot by a S.H.I.E.L.D agent that arrives on the scene with a team.","arc_events":false,"characters":["9","63"],"character_events":["Wolverine appears after being alerted by a former criminal mutant to the escape of Karl Lycos from The Raft.  He claims he is the only one who came as the others have a school to run.","Spider-Woman has difficulty believing that S.H.I.E.L.D is involved in illegal activities such as mining Vibranium or using Sauron to kill other mutants."],"arc_id":false,"previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(80, 6, 2005, 6, 22, 14, '1328135892.jpg', 'After Spider Woman fails to talk down the S.H.I.E.L.D agents, Yelena Belova, another ''Black Widow'' and the leader of the S.H.I.E.L.D agents opens fire as Iron Man flies them out of the way.  Wolverine incapacitates Yelena as Iron Man disarms the agents with a polar magnetic field.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nSpider Woman interrogates Yelena but they are interrupted by a Sauron who sets Yelena on fire and she runs into the jungle.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nLuke Cage takes down Sauron and they take him with them as they investigate an anomaly detected by Iron Man.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThey discover a S.H.I.E.L.D operation which has enslaved the natives and forced them to mine for Vibranium.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThey immediately attack the operation to free the slaves but Iron Man is forced to shield them when Maria Hill arrives and fires on the compound killing them all.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nCaptain America is enraged but Wolverine tells him that she might be telling the truth about not meaning to attack the New Avengers.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nTalking privately, Iron Man informs them that the files S.H.I.E.L.D gave them from The Raft were incomplete and tampered with.  S.H.I.E.L.D was holding prisoners who were declared dead.  They suspect a conspiracy.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nCaptain America offers them the chance to leave the team in light of the new information but Tony instead invites Wolverine to join over Captain America''s objections, who claims he is a murderer.  Tony points out that he is a samurai warrior, and that is different.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nYelena is seen badly burned and bandaged in a hospital bed as someone talks to her and offers her a chance to get everything back.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1328135892_737699300":{"comic":"14","issue_number":"6","year_published":"2005","month_published":"6","day_published":"22","image":"1328135892.jpg","comic_summary":"After Spider Woman fails to talk down the S.H.I.E.L.D agents, Yelena Belova, another ''Black Widow'' and the leader of the S.H.I.E.L.D agents opens fire as Iron Man flies them out of the way.  Wolverine incapacitates Yelena as Iron Man disarms the agents with a polar magnetic field.\\r\\n\\r\\nSpider Woman interrogates Yelena but they are interrupted by a Sauron who sets Yelena on fire and she runs into the jungle.\\r\\n\\r\\nLuke Cage takes down Sauron and they take him with them as they investigate an anomaly detected by Iron Man.\\r\\n\\r\\nThey discover a S.H.I.E.L.D operation which has enslaved the natives and forced them to mine for Vibranium.\\r\\n\\r\\nThey immediately attack the operation to free the slaves but Iron Man is forced to shield them when Maria Hill arrives and fires on the compound killing them all.\\r\\n\\r\\nCaptain America is enraged but Wolverine tells him that she might be telling the truth about not meaning to attack the New Avengers.\\r\\n\\r\\nTalking privately, Iron Man informs them that the files S.H.I.E.L.D gave them from The Raft were incomplete and tampered with.  S.H.I.E.L.D was holding prisoners who were declared dead.  They suspect a conspiracy.\\r\\n\\r\\nCaptain America offers them the chance to leave the team in light of the new information but Tony instead invites Wolverine to join over Captain America''s objections, who claims he is a murderer.  Tony points out that he is a samurai warrior, and that is different.\\r\\n\\r\\nYelena is seen badly burned and bandaged in a hospital bed as someone talks to her and offers her a chance to get everything back.","arc_events":false,"characters":["51"],"character_events":[""],"arc_id":false,"previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(81, 7, 2005, 7, 13, 14, '1328145731.jpg', 'Iron Man attends a meeting consisting of Stephen Strange, Reed Richards, Charles Xavier, Black Bolt and Namor.  They discuss the forming of The New Avengers and the prison breakout, but Tony wants to discuss just who the Sentry is.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn Long Island a girl is sunbathing when a large man grabs her by her pool and forces her to take him to his things which her father had bought.  Her father collects super-villain items and he bought the mans, he is The Wrecker.  He forces her into the car but as they pull out of the garage they are confronted by the New Avengers.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn the ensuing fight The Wrecker is more than able to hold his own again Wolverine, Luke Cage, Spiderman and Spider-Woman.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nMeanwhile, Captain America and Iron Man go to the Nevada Dessert where S.H.I.E.L.D has found The Sentry.  The Sentry explains that when he uses his power it creates The Void who attacks the planet and kills.  He claims it killed his wife but Iron Man has brought his wife along... and the man who created The Sentry, The Sentry is a comic book character.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1328145731_737699300":{"comic":"14","issue_number":"7","year_published":"2005","month_published":"7","day_published":"13","image":"1328145731.jpg","comic_summary":"Iron Man attends a meeting consisting of Stephen Strange, Reed Richards, Charles Xavier, Black Bolt and Namor.  They discuss the forming of The New Avengers and the prison breakout, but Tony wants to discuss just who the Sentry is.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn Long Island a girl is sunbathing when a large man grabs her by her pool and forces her to take him to his things which her father had bought.  Her father collects super-villain items and he bought the mans, he is The Wrecker.  He forces her into the car but as they pull out of the garage they are confronted by the New Avengers.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn the ensuing fight The Wrecker is more than able to hold his own again Wolverine, Luke Cage, Spiderman and Spider-Woman.\\r\\n\\r\\nMeanwhile, Captain America and Iron Man go to the Nevada Dessert where S.H.I.E.L.D has found The Sentry.  The Sentry explains that when he uses his power it creates The Void who attacks the planet and kills.  He claims it killed his wife but Iron Man has brought his wife along... and the man who created The Sentry, The Sentry is a comic book character.","arc_events":false,"characters":["51"],"character_events":[""],"arc_id":false,"previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(82, 8, 2005, 8, 3, 14, '1328227225.jpg', 'The Sentry reads his life in a comic book as the New Avengers and S.H.I.E.L.D agents look on.  They don''t know who The Sentry is beyond a comic book character, but they do know who Bob Reynolds is.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThe scene flashes back to a week prior where Tony Stark attempts to talk Logan into joining the New Avengers.  He eventually resorts to bribery, or ''trading'' as he calls it.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBack in the present they are still fighting The Wrecker.  Spider-Woman doesn''t fight, claiming she wants to help.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn Nevada, Bob Reynolds wife, Lindy, attempts to talk to him but he refuses to believe she is alive and he vanishes in a huge explosion of light.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nMeanwhile Spider-Woman has lulled The Wrecker into a slight trance as she asks him what he wants in life, but it is just stall tactic to distract him for Wolverine and the others to re-group and attack.  They manage to trap him in one of Spiderman''s webs.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nTony Stark orders them to Connecticut.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBob Reynolds has fallen asleep in front of his TV but is woken by Emma Frost appearing on his screen and talking to him.  He tells him to go outside where he finds an array of superheroes assembled.  Bob falls to his knees as he tells them he warned them that The Void was coming.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1328227225_737699300":{"comic":"14","issue_number":"8","year_published":"2005","month_published":"8","day_published":"3","image":"1328227225.jpg","comic_summary":"The Sentry reads his life in a comic book as the New Avengers and S.H.I.E.L.D agents look on.  They don''t know who The Sentry is beyond a comic book character, but they do know who Bob Reynolds is.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe scene flashes back to a week prior where Tony Stark attempts to talk Logan 