(83, 9, 2005, 8, 24, 14, '1328578637.jpg', 'The Illuminate are still in their meeting as the story jumps between the present and the future.  They are investigating Bob Reynolds a.k.a The Sentry.  Professor X discovers that someone has tampered with Reed Richards memories of The Sentry.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIn the present the assembled heroes who have gathered outside the home of Bob Reynolds find themselves under attack by The Void.  Whilst the others defend them, Emma Frost and Reed Richards show Bob a recording of himself explaining how he creates The Void and about himself and that if all else fails they should just kill him.  With Bob''s consent Emma enters his mind to help him deal with The Void.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nEmma finds that hidden behind his memories are scenes involving Mastermind and a mysterious figure.  Mastermind is explaining how he was able to alter his memories and make it so that Bob Reynolds would unknowingly alter the memories of everyone else and essentially erase The Sentry.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBob is horrified by the memory and flees into his mind, abandoning Emma.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1328578637_737699300":{"comic":"14","issue_number":"9","year_published":"2005","month_published":"8","day_published":"24","image":"1328578637.jpg","comic_summary":"The Illuminate are still in their meeting as the story jumps between the present and the future.  They are investigating Bob Reynolds a.k.a The Sentry.  Professor X discovers that someone has tampered with Reed Richards memories of The Sentry.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn the present the assembled heroes who have gathered outside the home of Bob Reynolds find themselves under attack by The Void.  Whilst the others defend them, Emma Frost and Reed Richards show Bob a recording of himself explaining how he creates The Void and about himself and that if all else fails they should just kill him.  With Bob''s consent Emma enters his mind to help him deal with The Void.\\r\\n\\r\\nEmma finds that hidden behind his memories are scenes involving Mastermind and a mysterious figure.  Mastermind is explaining how he was able to alter his memories and make it so that Bob Reynolds would unknowingly alter the memories of everyone else and essentially erase The Sentry.\\r\\n\\r\\nBob is horrified by the memory and flees into his mind, abandoning Emma.","arc_events":false,"characters":["51"],"character_events":[""],"arc_id":false,"previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(84, 10, 2005, 9, 21, 14, '1328579805.jpg', 'Whilst being held on board the S.H.I.E.L.D Hellicarrier, Mrs Lindy Reynolds, the wife of Bob Reynolds collapses whilst waiting with Mr. Jenkins, the man who wrote The Sentry comics.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nShe awakens to find herself with Emma Frost in her husbands mind.  Emma explains that she needs her help to bring her husband back.  She uses a memory of one of her first dates with a young Bob Reynolds which allows Emma to approach Bob again.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nEmma is able to talk to Bob and calm him which causes The Void to become motionless and give the heroes a chance to breathe.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThey leave his mind where the heroes pick themselves off of the floor.  The Avengers invite Bob to join them and Emma unlocks his powers fully.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nJarvis calls them back to the tower where The Sentry''s Watchtower has appeared atop the tower.  Bob explains he must have been hiding.  He enters the structure which he claims holds his life leaving the Avengers behind as they promise they will still be there.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBack with the Illuminate, Namor warns Tony to call them together should The Sentry start to slip.  Reed questions Tony about the rumours of S.H.I.E.L.D being in The Savage Land and if there is anything they need to worry about.  Tony tells them there is nothing they need to know.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1328579805_737699300":{"comic":"14","issue_number":"10","year_published":"2005","month_published":"9","day_published":"21","image":"1328579805.jpg","comic_summary":"Whilst being held on board the S.H.I.E.L.D Hellicarrier, Mrs Lindy Reynolds, the wife of Bob Reynolds collapses whilst waiting with Mr. Jenkins, the man who wrote The Sentry comics.\\r\\n\\r\\nShe awakens to find herself with Emma Frost in her husbands mind.  Emma explains that she needs her help to bring her husband back.  She uses a memory of one of her first dates with a young Bob Reynolds which allows Emma to approach Bob again.\\r\\n\\r\\nEmma is able to talk to Bob and calm him which causes The Void to become motionless and give the heroes a chance to breathe.\\r\\n\\r\\nThey leave his mind where the heroes pick themselves off of the floor.  The Avengers invite Bob to join them and Emma unlocks his powers fully.\\r\\n\\r\\nJarvis calls them back to the tower where The Sentry''s Watchtower has appeared atop the tower.  Bob explains he must have been hiding.  He enters the structure which he claims holds his life leaving the Avengers behind as they promise they will still be there.\\r\\n\\r\\nBack with the Illuminate, Namor warns Tony to call them together should The Sentry start to slip.  Reed questions Tony about the rumours of S.H.I.E.L.D being in The Savage Land and if there is anything they need to worry about.  Tony tells them there is nothing they need to know.","arc_events":false,"characters":["51"],"character_events":[""],"arc_id":false,"previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(85, 21, 2005, 12, 14, 13, '1330085863.jpg', 'One year prior to M-Day:<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWilliam Stryker saves a man from a car crash by preventing him from entering it.  He uses the event to entice the man to join him.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nPresent Day:<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWhilst Forge presents Surge with improved gloves, the other students are discussing what will happen to those of them who have been de-powered.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nStryker appears on the news and essentially tells the world that M-Day was an act of God and that it is up to them to finish what he started.  Icarus buys into the rhetoric and gets into an argument with the others, Prodigy insists they stick together but Hellion accuses him of not being part of ''them'' any more as he is now a human.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nSofia over hears him and argues with him before storming off.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nAs Surge and Hellion are about to get into a fight, Wolverine interrupts and introduces them to X-23, Laura, he calls her his sister.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nProdigy talks Surge out of the fight by offering them a better way to let of steam.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nEmma and Scott argue over allowing X-23 to stay as Emma says she is too dangerous, but Scott is willing to trust Wolverine''s judgement and says that Laura is staying.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nProdigy shows the others the Danger Cave he made using the combined knowledge of Hank McCoy and Kitty Pryde.  Hellion and his team have followed them but Prodigy still activates the room causing a power outage in the rest of the mansion.  They attempt to run a few of the original X-Men''s missions but there are few glitches.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\n10 days from the present:<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nElixir walks into the infirmary to find Beast and Emma working on the injured Icarus.  Icarus wakes up and begins screaming for them to leave him alone.', 5, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1330085863_737699300":{"comic":"13","issue_number":"21","year_published":"2005","month_published":"12","day_published":"14","image":"1330085863.jpg","comic_summary":"One year prior to M-Day:\\r\\n\\r\\nWilliam Stryker saves a man from a car crash by preventing him from entering it.  He uses the event to entice the man to join him.\\r\\n\\r\\nPresent Day:\\r\\n\\r\\nWhilst Forge presents Surge with improved gloves, the other students are discussing what will happen to those of them who have been de-powered.\\r\\n\\r\\nStryker appears on the news and essentially tells the world that M-Day was an act of God and that it is up to them to finish what he started.  Icarus buys into the rhetoric and gets into an argument with the others, Prodigy insists they stick together but Hellion accuses him of not being part of ''them'' any more as he is now a human.\\r\\n\\r\\nSofia over hears him and argues with him before storming off.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs Surge and Hellion are about to get into a fight, Wolverine interrupts and introduces them to X-23, Laura, he calls her his sister.\\r\\n\\r\\nProdigy talks Surge out of the fight by offering them a better way to let of steam.\\r\\n\\r\\nEmma and Scott argue over allowing X-23 to stay as Emma says she is too dangerous, but Scott is willing to trust Wolverine''s judgement and says that Laura is staying.\\r\\n\\r\\nProdigy shows the others the Danger Cave he made using the combined knowledge of Hank McCoy and Kitty Pryde.  Hellion and his team have followed them but Prodigy still activates the room causing a power outage in the rest of the mansion.  They attempt to run a few of the original X-Men''s missions but there are few glitches.\\r\\n\\r\\n10 days from the present:\\r\\n\\r\\nElixir walks into the infirmary to find Beast and Emma working on the injured Icarus.  Icarus wakes up and begins screaming for them to leave him alone.","arc_events":false,"characters":["51"],"character_events":[""],"arc_id":"5","previous_event_id":false,"next_event_id":false}}', 0, '', 'published', '2012-06-16 13:00:00'),
(86, 22, 2006, 1, 11, 13, '1330187019.jpg', 'Six months before M-Day:<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWilliam Stryker aids Matthew Risman in saving his family by warning him to get them out of the house.  He uses this event to recruit Risman to his cause.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nPresent Day:<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThe New X-Men are still trying out Prodigy''s Danger Cave but Tag and Icarus don''t feel right and leave so Cessily invites a nearby X-23 to join them.  She then proceeds to consistently save Hellion from numerous assaults much to his annoyance.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nIcarus returns and informs them that Dani is leaving.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWither over hears Julian, Santo and Cessily discussing the fact that the de-powered mutants may be sent home and he may be sent away because he is too dangerous.  He runs off before he hears Julian assure Cessily that he won''t let that happen.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nDani says good bye to her students after which Scott assigns Laura to bunk with Sooraya.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThat night Cessily notices that Kevin has left but Julian is too busy trying to get Sofia to talk to him to help her find him.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nEmma uses her telepathy to torture X-23 with hallucinations of her mother, but she sees through them.  Emma warns her that she will not permit her to stay.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nSeven Days from the present:<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nStryker and his armies assemble and arm themselves.', 5, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1330187019_737699300":{"comic":"13","issue_number":"22","year_published":"2006","month_published":"1","day_published":"11","image":"1330187019.jpg","comic_summary":"Six months before M-Day:\\r\\n\\r\\nWilliam Stryker aids Matthew Risman in saving his family by warning him to get them out of the house.  