(88, 1, 2004, 5, 26, 8, '1337027389.jpg', 'A young girl awakens from a nightmare and is comforted by a woman in lab coat as a mysterious figure watches from the shadows.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nAs Kitty Pryde returns to the X-Mansion she reminisces about her life and experiences that she had there.  She eventually phases through a wall to discover that she is late and that Emma Frost has already begun the assembly.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nAs Kitty joins Scott and Hank on the chairs behind Emma on the platform, Emma informs the students that she will be a new teacher at the school.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nIn the middle of her speech Sentinels seemingly attack the auditorium, tearing through the ceiling and sending the students into a panic.  But it was only a Danger Room simulation which Emma claims was to teach them a lesson: "They will always hate us."<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nScott wakes up next Emma to find an angry Logan perched on the end of the bed.  Logan thinks that Scott is dishonoring Jean'' memory and they fight.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nLater the team is assembled in the the Danger Room and Hank berates the pair for the example they set for the students.  Scott declares that he is reassembling the X-Men to handle the things that superheroes should be doing and that he wants them all on the team.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nKavita Rao, the woman in the lab coat and the girl she comforted are preparing to go on stage to make an announcement.  She tells the world that mutants are not better or worse than normal humans, they are a people with a disease, and now they have a cure.<br /><br />\r\n<br /><br />\r\nMeanwhile the mysterious figure attacks an upscale party whilst the X-Men gear up to respond.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 100002077828287, '{"1331693736_100002077828287":{"comic":"8","issue_number":"1","year_published":"2004","month_published":"5","day_published":"26","image":"1331693736.jpg","comic_summary":"As Kitty Pryde r