(170, 13, 1965, 2, 10, 1, '1372374127.jpg', '<p>After the Avengers stop several crimes created by the Maggia, on of the leaders of the Maggia is summoned through an image projection system to their true leader, Count Nefaria.</p>\r\n<p>The Count is the richest noble in Europe, he heads the Maggia crime syndicate and he decides he needs to deal with the Avengers himself. &nbsp;He has his castle moved to the United States brick by brick and then opens it to the public and invites the Avengers.</p>\r\n<p>Out of pure curiosity the team, along with Rick Jones and the Teen Brigade head to the Count''s castle. &nbsp;Rick and the Brigade wait outside whilst the Avengers head inside and are surprised that the Count has actually prepared quarters for them. &nbsp;They suspect nothing and gratefully accept.</p>\r\n<p>The seemingly modern day lights in the asigned rooms are actually a Time Transcender Beams that make the Avengers appear to have frozen in time. &nbsp;Count Nefaria uses this opportunity to make holographic images of the Avengers. &nbsp;He sends them to the Pentagon where he demands the govenrment surrender so that the Avengers can rule. &nbsp;The government refuses and the fake Avengers declare war with the US Government.</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile Rick Jones and the Teen Brigade become suspicious and attempt to sneak into the castle to find out what is happening but they are quickly found and thrown in the dungeons by the Count''s Maggia.</p>\r\n<p>The Count releases the Avengers from his hold leaving them unaware that he has actually done anything. &nbsp;As the Avengers leave the castle they are instantly attacked by US troops, they are hard pressed to defend themselves without hurting the soldiers so they retreat to their emergency headquarters.</p>\r\n<p>Ant Man and The Wasp discover the newspaper headlines declaring them wanted for treason. &nbsp;The team determines thatthey have been impersonated and that is must tie in with the Count as they were attacked as soon as they left.</p>\r\n<p>Whilst the Avengers head back to the Castle to confront Count Nefaria the Fantastic Four are warned by the Pentagon to stay off the streets in case they are attacked in the wake of the anti super-powered sentiment brought on by the recent confrontation with the Avengers.</p>\r\n<p>Rick and the Teen Brigade try to contact Iron Man using the hidden communications device they carry but they are unable to. &nbsp;The Count intercepts the call he has them moved to a new cell where the walls trap them in a narrow space that one touch will put them into a state of suspended animation.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 737699300, '{"1372835338":{"737699300":null}}', 0, '', 'waiting', '2013-06-27 16:02:07'),
