(95, 2, 2004, 6, 23, 8, '1332041427.jpg', 'Kavita Rao shows her audience a video of two police officers attending the scene of when the little girl, Tildie Soames, mutation manifested and killed her parents and one of the officers.  She tells them that Tildie volunteered to help test the cure.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nMeanwhile, the X-Men evaluate the hostage situation at the up-scale party.  They determine that the mysterious figure who appears cold on the thermal scanners.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWhilst Kitty begins phasing the hostages out covertly, Emma begins to play with the minds of the soldiers creating distractions, but the mysterious figure tells them to ''turn up their scramblers'' to defend against her.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nThe X-Men attack quickly, taking out the armed men, but Wolverine determines that the figure set this up as a test for them and a fight ensues.  The figure declares himself ''Ord, of the Breakworld''.  As the X-Men appear defeated, Lockheed appears and sets him on fire causing him to flee.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWhilst the X-Men speak to the press one of them asks Hank about the ''mutant cure'', Hank has no idea what he is talking about.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nBack at the Mansion the X-Men try to deal with the fall out from the news of a ''cure''.  They consider the possibility that the attack by Ord and the announcement were connected.  Emma and Logan wish to take drastic measures to the point of killing her.  Emma because she fears the ''cure'' will be forced on them and Logan because she called him a disease.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nHank breaks into Benetech, the company producing the ''cure'', he confronts Kavita Rao.  But he tells her he isn''t there to stop her... he just wants to know if it works.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 100002077828287, '{"1332041427_100002077828287":{"comic":"8","issue_number":"2","year_published"