(96, 3, 2004, 7, 28, 8, '1332095803.jpg', 'Wing is talking with Kitty about what it means to him to be able to fly, and his history.  Kitty assures him that no one will force the ''cure'' on him.  He doesn''t believe her.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nHank informs the X-Men that Kavita Rao gave her the ''cure'' and that he will be a day at the most.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nMeanwhile, Ord is furious with Kavita for handing it to them.  He rants at her and about the X-Men but she seems completely indifferent and unafraid of him.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nScott shows Nick Fury one of the weapons they took off the mercenaries and Fury recognizes it but doesn''t know how they got it.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nFury insinuates that Ord could be a mutant and Scott takes offence.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nLogan confronts Hank about the sample.  He says that Emma couldn''t help but overhear his thoughts that he wanted to be normal again.  He warns him to flush the ''cure'' or he will.  They wind up fighting as Hank worries he is devolving.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nWhen their fight breaks into the corridors and in front of the students, Emma takes control of them and assembles the team in the Danger Room.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nScott assigns them tasks but Kitty asks if they should find the Professor, Emma warns that he is not running the team and they won''t be running to him for every little thing.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<br /><br /><br />\r\nHank''s investigation reveal startling news about who they are running tests on, a body.  He tells Scott and Emma and Scott believes it is Jean.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 100002077828287, '{"1332095803_100002077828287":{"comic":"8","issue_number":"3","year_published":"2004","month_published":"7","day_published":"28","image":"1332095803.jpg","comic_summary":"Wing is talking with Kitty about what it means to him to be able to f